In order to be able to compile the verifier (Main.hs), you have to
install (the correct version of) Z3 first.

Do this:

1. Clone the Z3 repository from github somewhere appropriate:

  > git clone git@github.com:Z3Prover/z3.git

2. Make it go to the correct version (4.08) compatible with the Hackage Z3 library:

  > cd z3
  > git checkout d420706

3. Make sure you have Python3 installed (and callable through the "python" command):
   (this will depend on your OS!)

  > sudo apt install python3
  > sudo apt install python-is-python3

4. Configure & make & install:
   (this will depend on your OS!)

  > ./configure
  > cd build
  > make
  > make install

5. Done!
